      <description>I'm not sure about the software the EQ Players site is using (Java?), but I found on my own PHP and Ruby sites that the session would only maintain for a relatively short time, regardless of what I did. I ended up having to implement a second cookie for anyone that wanted longer login time, then using that cookie to restart closed sessions.  It was extra work, but it paid off in the end by allowing people to stay signed in forever, should they so desire.   Perhaps this is a similar issue?&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
